=Description=

"Our purpose is to channel information about mining issues and encourage jewelers to become
informed advocates for social and environmental responsibility. Susan Kingsley and Christina Miller
began working together because of their dismay on learning how precious metals were sourced. Each
had researched the social and environmental harm caused by gold mining and they shared a deep
concern about the field of jewelry and metalsmithing. Virtually no one in their field was aware of
environmental impacts of the materials upon which they depend. As metalsmiths themselves, they
decided to take action" 

